headline: Centene Housing Grant Highlights Community Focus And Undervalued Stock Debate
summary: Centene Foundation and Meridian Health Plan of Illinois awarded a $2.2 million grant to Safer Foundation. The funding will support affordable housing for underserved and justice involved individuals in Chicago. The initiative aims to address social determinants of health by expanding housing access in vulnerable communities. For investors watching NYSE:CNC, this grant adds context around how Centene is tying its healthcare presence to community level support. The stock closed at $43.32,...
